The root mean square error (RMSE) is the residues given by the difference between the actual and predicted values, obtiaied from a mean square error. Also this is an error measure used on values observed on the system state. The RMSE given in the Eq. 17 gives the estimation of the model predictions and is defined as the square root of the average squared error:17RMSE=∑i=1nXobs,i−Xmodel,i2n\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ RMSE=\sqrt{\frac{{\displaystyle {\sum}_{i=1}^n{\left({X}_{obs,i}-{X}_{mo\;del,i}\right)}^2}}{n}} $$\end{document}
